      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <h2>The GRIP Diamond.</h2>
        </div>

        <p>
          Every organisation already has a GTM system. The question is not whether it exists, but how balanced it is. The GRIP Diamond makes that balance visible in one view.
        </p>

        <p><strong>Guidance</strong> provides clarity of strategy, ICP and focus.<br>
           Without it, teams work hard but not in the same direction.</p>

        <p><strong>Resources</strong> represent the people, tools and infrastructure that carry the work.<br>
           When this layer is stretched or misaligned, execution becomes fragile.</p>

        <p><strong>Implementation</strong> is the discipline behind your motions, processes and operating rhythm.<br>
           It turns intentions into consistent behaviour.</p>

        <p><strong>Performance</strong> shows the outcomes across demand, pipeline, retention and expansion.<br>
           It is the visible expression of the underlying system, never the root cause.</p>

        <p>
          The GRIP health card shows the strength of each force as a score. The GRIP Diamond turns that same information into a shape you can see at a glance.
        </p>

        <p>
          The GTM Framework uses this shape as a starting point. It connects strategy, process, tools and teams into one operating system so that improvements are made in the right place and in the right order.
        </p>

      </div>
    </section>

